  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nwhen clear the db path(even in a clean directory), thenstart the program with flags: --checkpoint-sync-url=https://sync.invis.tools/ --genesis-beacon-api-url=https://sync.invis.tools/ which copied from here: \"https://docs.prylabs.network/docs/prysm-usage/checkpoint-sync#option-1-configure-checkpoint-sync-via-network-request\", it shows me error:\r\n\r\n[2023-09-15 18:16:24] WARN flags: Running on Ethereum Mainnet\r\n[2023-09-15 18:16:24] WARN node: In order to receive transaction fees from proposing blocks, you must provide flag --suggested-fee-recipient with a valid ethereum address when starting your beacon node. Please see our documentation for more information on this requirement (https://docs.prylabs.network/docs/execution-node/fee-recipient).\r\n[2023-09-15 18:16:24] INFO node: Checking DB database-path=/root/.eth2/beaconchaindata\r\n[2023-09-15 18:16:24] INFO db: Opening Bolt DB at /root/.eth2/beaconchaindata/beaconchain.db\r\n[2023-09-15 18:16:24] **WARN database contains genesis with htr=0x7e76880eb67bbdc86250aa578958e9d0675e64e714337855204fb5abaaf82c2b, ignoring remote genesis state parameter**\r\n\r\nand then, it will no longer output any things.\r\n\r\nI think it's a bug: it will produce the db when there's no db file, whatever your params are.\r\n\r\nThere's some same issues, but i don't think it's fixed:\r\n1. https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/issues/11525\r\n2. https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/issues/12206\n\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\n\n```text\ntried for v4.0.6, also failed.\n```\n\n\n### üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\n\n1. new directory\r\n2. start the program with sync flags\n\n### üî• Error\n\n_No response_\n\n### üåç Platform(s)\n\nLinux (x86)\n\n### What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)\n\nv4.0.8, v4.0.6\n\n### Anything else relevant (validator index / public key)?\n\n_No response_",
